<section xml:id="object-mapping-preferences" version="5.0" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
                                                       xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
                                                       xmlns:xl="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" >
  <title>Object mapping preferences</title>
  <anchor role="helpid" condition="prefPageObjectMapContextId" xml:id="object-mapping-preferences.prefPageObjectMapContextId" xreflabel="Object Mapping Preferences"/>
  <anchor role="helpid" condition="objectMapEditorContextId" xml:id="object-mapping-preferences.objectMapEditorContextId" xreflabel="Object Mapping"/>
  <figure>
    <title>Object Mapping Preference Dialog</title>
    <mediaobject>
      <imageobject>
        <imagedata fileref="images/objectmappingprefs.png"/>
      </imageobject>
      <textobject><phrase>Object Mapping Preference
      Dialog</phrase></textobject>
    </mediaobject>
  </figure>
  <para>
    You can access the object mapping preferences from
    <emphasis>Test - Object Mapping</emphasis> in the preferences
    dialog.
  </para>
  <orderedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Select whether you want the ITE to display how many nodes
        are contained in each category in the Object Mapping Editor.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Choose which keystrokes or mouse buttons you want to use to
        collect components in the Object Mapping Mode.
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </orderedlist>
  <para role="tip">
    If your AUT does not accept keystrokes, set the object
    collection preference to a mouse button combined with a modifier
    key.
  </para>
</section>